><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\"><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\"><svg role=\"img\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><g><title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path></g></svg></button><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>There is a spiritual law beneath Thanksgiving that most people never notice:</p><p><strong>Gratitude brings you back into the present moment.</strong></p><p><strong>Anxiety pulls you out of it.</strong></p><p>Every moment of fear, dread, agitation, or internal scrambling is a retreat from <em>now</em>. We often avoid the present because something in the moment feels threatening. Something stirs restlessness or grief or discomfort, and we try to slip out the side door.</p><p>But God is only ever found in the present moment.</p><p>He names Himself <em>I AM</em>.</p><p>Not <em>I was</em>.<br>Not <em>I will be</em>.<br><strong>I AM here.</strong></p><p>Thanksgiving is the act of re-entering the place where God actually is.</p><h3>Anxiety Leads Us Away From Presence</h3><p>People assume anxiety is about the future. It’s also resistance to being <em>here</em>. The heart senses ambiguity or pain in the present moment and tries to outrun it. We get busy or irritable. We distract ourselves. We fixate on something to control.</p><p>Some people even avoid holidays, family gatherings, quiet evenings, or prayer because silence exposes the ache.</p><p>But if God is present, the…</p>"}